thread.title: J.T. Barrett To Start Against Rutgers
thread.title_full: J.T. Barrett To Start Against Rutgers

title: J.T. Barrett To Start Against Rutgers
text:
By 10TV Web Staff Tuesday October 20, 2015 1:44 PM COLUMBUS, Ohio - 
Coach Urban Meyer has announced that J.T. Barrett will start over Cardale Jones during Saturday night’s game at Rutgers. 
Meyer made the announcement Tuesday afternoon during the Big Ten teleconference. 
The decision comes in the wake of Saturday night’s game against Penn State, where Barrett threw for two scores and ran for over 100 yards with two touchdowns on the ground. 
Jones was only 9-15 for 84 yards. 
When asked last week if the offense was running better with Barrett currently, Meyer replied that it was doing better against Penn State. 
Meyer added that anytime there’s a change at a position it’s a delicate decision especially with the quarterback spot. 
“Someone made the comment ‘Do you really care who plays at quarterback’ the other day and absolutely we care,” he said. “It’s not number 16 and 12, those are people that we care about deeply and we’re not ashamed to say that.” 
The Buckeyes are back on the road this weekend as they will travel to Piscataway, N.J. to face Rutgers Saturday at 8 p.m. ©2015 by 10TV.com. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed. Currently in Columbus
